---
// src/pages/resources/design-kit/chameleon-creator.astro
import Layout from '../../../components/layout/Layout.astro';
import '../../../styles/design-kit-detail.css';
import '../../../styles/design-kit-tool.css';
---

<Layout
  title="Chameleon Creator | Design Kit | The eLearning Company"
  description="An honest look at Chameleon Creator — what it does well, where it struggles, and when it's the right tool for the job."
>
  <section class="section section--yellow component-hero">
    <div class="container">
      <nav class="breadcrumb" aria-label="Breadcrumb">
        <a href="/">Home</a>
        <span class="breadcrumb-sep">/</span>
        <a href="/resources">Resources</a>
        <span class="breadcrumb-sep">/</span>
        <a href="/resources/design-kit">Design kit</a>
        <span class="breadcrumb-sep">/</span>
        <span class="breadcrumb-current">Chameleon Creator</span>
      </nav>

      <span class="pill-meta hero-pill">eLearning tool</span>
      <h1 class="display display-xl page-title">
        Chameleon<br />
        <span class="accent-blue">Creator.</span>
      </h1>
      <p class="lede page-subtitle">
        Chameleon Creator is an Australian and New Zealand-built authoring tool that bundles design, hosting, and analytics in a single platform. It's positioned for L&amp;D teams who want courses that look distinct without hiring a designer.
      </p>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--paper tool-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="tool-meta">
        <div class="tool-meta-item">
          <span class="meta tool-meta-label">Type</span>
          <p class="tool-meta-value">Web-based HTML5 authoring + hosting + analytics</p>
        </div>
        <div class="tool-meta-item">
          <span class="meta tool-meta-label">Output</span>
          <p class="tool-meta-value">SCORM, secure shared URLs, hosted delivery (their LMS-lite)</p>
        </div>
        <div class="tool-meta-item">
          <span class="meta tool-meta-label">Pricing</span>
          <p class="tool-meta-value">From around $US1,440/year + GST. 14-day free trial.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="tool-meta-item">
          <span class="meta tool-meta-label">Best for</span>
          <p class="tool-meta-value">L&amp;D teams in mid-to-large organisations wanting branded, design-led courses without an external designer</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--paper-deep tool-strengths-section">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="section-kicker">Strengths</span>
      <h2 class="display display-md section-title">What it's great at.</h2>

      <div class="tool-points">
        <div class="tool-point">
          <h3 class="heading-sm">Design-first templates</h3>
          <p>Chameleon's templates are visibly more designed than the default <a href="/resources/design-kit/articulate-rise">Rise</a> aesthetic. Custom colours, fonts, illustrations, and 25+ interactive elements come pre-built. Courses don't look identical to every other course on the same tool — a real concern with more standardised platforms.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="tool-point">
          <h3 class="heading-sm">Built-in hosting and analytics</h3>
          <p>You can skip the LMS entirely. Publish to Chameleon's hosting, share secure URLs, and get engagement analytics out of the box. Useful when training extends to contractors, suppliers, or external audiences who don't have a company email.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="tool-point">
          <h3 class="heading-sm">Responsive output</h3>
          <p>Fully responsive HTML5. Phones, tablets, desktop — all handled without manual tuning. Comparable to <a href="/resources/design-kit/articulate-rise">Rise</a> in this respect, and a clear win over <a href="/resources/design-kit/articulate-storyline">Storyline</a>.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="tool-point">
          <h3 class="heading-sm">WCAG 2.0 accessibility baseline</h3>
          <p>Content can be built to WCAG 2.0 standards with the tool's guidance. Accessibility hints are surfaced as you build, rather than retroactively audited — which catches issues earlier than most tools.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="tool-point">
          <h3 class="heading-sm">Local support</h3>
          <p>Support team in Australia and New Zealand, dedicated account managers, sub-24-hour response times. For organisations in those time zones, this is meaningfully better than the US-based support most authoring tools offer.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--paper tool-weaknesses-section">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="section-kicker">Weaknesses</span>
      <h2 class="display display-md section-title">Where it struggles.</h2>

      <div class="tool-points">
        <div class="tool-point">
          <h3 class="heading-sm">No built-in audio or voiceover</h3>
          <p>You can't generate or record audio inside Chameleon. Voiceover has to be produced externally — recorded, AI-generated, or commissioned — then uploaded. A persistent point of friction in user reviews, and unusual for a platform at this price point in 2026.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="tool-point">
          <h3 class="heading-sm">Smaller ecosystem</h3>
          <p>Fewer templates, fewer community resources, fewer training videos than the <a href="/resources/design-kit/articulate-storyline">Articulate</a> ecosystem. If you hit an unusual problem, the answer probably isn't on a forum somewhere — you'll be asking the support team directly.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="tool-point">
          <h3 class="heading-sm">No complex branching or state tracking</h3>
          <p>Branching is supported, but not at the depth of <a href="/resources/design-kit/articulate-storyline">Storyline</a>. There's no variable system to track cumulative learner state, and complex <a href="/resources/design-kit/branching-scenarios">scenarios</a> with multi-decision consequences will hit the tool's ceiling.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="tool-point">
          <h3 class="heading-sm">Tied to Chameleon's hosting model</h3>
          <p>The "skip SCORM" advantage is also a lock-in risk. Courses hosted in Chameleon's platform are easy to deliver, but moving them out later — to a corporate LMS, to another vendor — requires re-authoring. SCORM export still works, but the hosted features don't carry across.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="tool-point">
          <h3 class="heading-sm">Less mature than Articulate</h3>
          <p>The product is younger than Articulate's tools and still maturing. Some users report a clunky interface in places, occasional limitations in template flexibility, and gaps in features that mature tools handle without comment.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--navy tool-decision-section">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="section-kicker">Decision</span>
      <h2 class="display display-md section-title">
        When Chameleon is <span class="mark--lilac">the right call</span>.
      </h2>

      <div class="decision-grid">
        <div class="decision-col">
          <h3 class="heading-md decision-heading">Pick Chameleon when</h3>
          <ul class="decision-list">
            <li>You're an internal L&amp;D team in mid-to-large ANZ organisations.</li>
            <li>Brand distinctiveness matters — your courses can't look like everyone else's.</li>
            <li>You want hosting and analytics without buying a separate LMS.</li>
            <li>You're delivering to external audiences (contractors, suppliers, customers) who don't have access to your LMS.</li>
            <li>Local support and Australian working hours are valuable.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
        <div class="decision-col decision-col--alt">
          <h3 class="heading-md decision-heading">Pick something else when</h3>
          <ul class="decision-list">
            <li>You need deep <a href="/resources/design-kit/branching-scenarios">branching</a>, simulations, or variable-driven logic — use <a href="/resources/design-kit/articulate-storyline">Storyline</a>.</li>
            <li>You need voiceover or audio generation inside the tool — Chameleon doesn't have it; <a href="/resources/design-kit/mindsmith">Mindsmith</a> or <a href="/resources/design-kit/articulate-rise">Articulate 360</a> do.</li>
            <li>The course volume is small (one a year) — the subscription is hard to justify at that scale.</li>
            <li>The ecosystem and community size matters — <a href="/resources/design-kit/articulate-rise">Articulate</a> has decades of head start.</li>
            <li>You need real-time multi-author collaboration with element-level comments — <a href="/resources/design-kit/parta">Parta</a> is built for that.</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--paper scenarios-section">
    <div class="container">
      <span class="section-kicker">When we'd reach for Chameleon</span>
      <h2 class="display display-md section-title">In practice.</h2>

      <div class="scenarios-grid">
        <div class="scenario-card">
          <span class="meta scenario-num">01</span>
          <h3 class="heading-sm">Brand-led onboarding programs</h3>
          <p>Organisations with strong brand standards that want their training to visibly belong to them, not look like a generic Rise course.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="scenario-card">
          <span class="meta scenario-num">02</span>
          <h3 class="heading-sm">External-facing learning</h3>
          <p>Training for contractors, channel partners, or customers who don't sit inside the corporate LMS. Chameleon's hosted delivery solves the access problem cleanly.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="scenario-card">
          <span class="meta scenario-num">03</span>
          <h3 class="heading-sm">L&amp;D teams without dedicated designers</h3>
          <p>Where the L&amp;D team is small or shared with HR, the design-led templates lift the visual quality of courses above what the same team would produce in a more open tool.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="scenario-card">
          <span class="meta scenario-num">04</span>
          <h3 class="heading-sm">Compliance with analytics</h3>
          <p>Compliance training where the analytics matter — completion rates, engagement, drop-off points — and the team doesn't want to wrestle with SCORM and LMS reporting.</p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="section section--lilac final-cta-section">
    <div class="container">
      <div class="cta-content">
        <h2 class="display display-lg cta-title">
          Need a course built<br />
          <span class="accent-blue">in your tool?</span>
        </h2>
        <p class="lede cta-text">
          We can build your eLearning in Chameleon Creator, or advise on what other tools may suit you. Three-week delivery, transparent pricing, zero drama.
        </p>
        <div class="cta-buttons">
          <a href="/contact" class="btn btn--primary">Get a quote</a>
          <a href="/resources/design-kit" class="btn btn--secondary">Back to design kit</a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </section>
</Layout>

